reviews: THE PEOPLE is by far one of the best hotels in Paris, great location (Belleville) amazing team on the frontdesk and specially at the bar, and no matter the request or issue they handle every situation in the most professional way!

Such an amazing experience at Les Piaules- The People hostel in Belleville. I am a solo female traveller and I stayed in 2 mixed dorms (8 bunks & 6 bunks) and felt so comfortable and safe. The beds are warm and cozy, the rooms and bathrooms are clean and the shower is hot and quite spacious. The rooftop terrace has Eiffel Tower & Sacre Coeur views and is perfect for admiring the beauty of Paris from above. The staff are super friendly and helpful and speak great English and the bar and patio area is a great place to hang out and meet other travellers! I 100% recommend this hostel for anyone travelling to Paris!!

Great two night stay with the family. Lots of posts saying it didn't feel safe but we felt entirely safe there. Beds were comfy, jazz jam was great.....only downside was checkout was at 12 but the cleaners kept coming in wanting to change the beds so it felt like we were being rushed out. But overall it was a great little place!

This is the best hostel I have ever been.

All the staff members have been extremely kind and proactive for the whole stay.

Bathroom and toilets are extremely clean and nice, there is a hairdryer provided as well.
It was my first trip as a solo traveller. I stayed in a female dorm and I felt the area was safe and well connected also at night.

I loved the beds: very clean bed sheets, very comfortable bed and I loved the curtain blind. Next to each bed there is a European socket. There is a dedicated space for luggage which you can lock with your own locker.
The bar downstairs is very nice and offers the possibility to buy breakfast for cheap price and other meals for a reasonable price. The Caesar salad was one of the best ones I have ever had.

One negative note: I booked directly on the hostel's website because it said that all taxes were included instead of Hostelworld which was explicitly saying that the local tax was not included. However, when I arrived, I was requested to pay extra for the local tax, so probably next time I will book from Hostelworld's website which allows also to keep in touch and arrange events with other solo travelers in the city.

As a whole it was a great experience and I definitely recommend it, also for women solo travelers.
Thank you. I will definitely come back soon 🙂

The hotel was wonderful and it exceeded my expectations. The bed was extremely comfortable and the room spacious and clean. I didnt Eat so i Can't Really rate the food, although others looked like they were enjoying the food .i Loved the Downtown location of the hotel.

It was a very nice place and the bed curtains gives a great privacy that many hostels don’t have. My single complaint would be the showers that were a bit cold. All in all, was a wonderful place, very clean and with great staff as well, I recommend it.

Virginie was a very warm welcoming hostess, she even offered us something for breakfast that we never expected but warmly appreciated. To add to this, she was very helpful when we sought advice on how to reach Versailles, giving us very specific guide on what subway/train to take. We reached Versailles without any problem.
Her place is also surrounded by restaurants, eateries and near the mrt. You will not regret your stay in her house, highly recommended!!

I don't expect luxury from a hostel, but I do expect cleanliness.

On the surface the hostel appears clean. Most importantly, the bed sheets and mattress are clean. However, look beyond that and you'll see it's filthy and obviously never given a deep clean. Down the side of the lower bunk there is what must be months and months of rotten food, old socks, dirt and dust that has been allowed to collect. No wonder the room smells so musty and stuffy. My bunk had blood streaks from a squashed bug (and live mosquitoes flying about), as well as sticky finger prints all over the bed panels and window.

Furthermore, the noise level is crazy. I understand on a Friday people want to party so the bar was blasting out music and the 1st floor rooms are not sound proof - I actually didn't mind that. What annoyed me was the fact that they were blasting music through the speakers in the 1st floor toilet/shower rooms. WHY?! This made the room and hallways even noisier.

Its only saving grace is the location (and free wi-fi). It can feel a bit dodgy walking through there alone as a single woman at night, but so can any big city... The hostel is close to some great bars, restaurants, and tourist attractions (Père Lachaise Cemetery, for example). I'd recommend hiring a bike to get around - there's quite a few Vélib' bike stations a short walk away.

Poor customer service, poor breakfast for the price, rooms extremely small, dirty, uncomfortable beds, no atmosphere but the bar. Not a nice location. Booked through Booking.com reading reviews and looking at pictures, but was a huge surprise and disappointment when arrived. Not clean bathrooms.

Great place to stay in Paris, the staff are friendly. Also the rooms have lockers and curtains on the bed which is positive. Location of hostel is quite far out from ‘ attractions’ but there’s a metro station nearby so it doesn’t matter.
Book in advance for cheaper rates.

The bed had a curtain and own lamp and power outlet, which made staying comfortable. There was a nice rooftop guests could go on, giving a nice view of the neighborhood. And a voucher for a small welcome drink was also nice. There was no common kitchen guests could use, but it was ok to eat outside food in the lobby. Overall, a good hostel and would recommend!

The staff is friendly, the accommodations are comfortable (with the privacy of bed curtains), and it is a good environment to meet other travelers in. I am glad I stayed here. Also in a neighborhood that has good restaurants and bars, and close enough to get to the major Paris sites.

The best hostel I ever stayed at. The beds are very comfortable, lockers are spacious. The showers were pretty clean. The atmosphere of the place and the incredible staff were definitely the best part though. I’ll definitely stay here again next time I’m in Paris.

The staff is very friendly and the location is very close to metro stations. The area around the hostel has a lot of bars and restaurants. The A/C at my room was amazing during the hot weather of Paris . The lockers are too big to have big luggage.

What i didn't like there was one toilette only without any kind of ventilation at each floor which isn't suitable for all guests. The cleaning ladies entered the room while the people were sleeping to arrange it before the check out time.

Stayed there for 3 nights and the bathrooms and beds are all pretty nice. The shower was one of our favorites of all the hostels we stayed in and the beds were decently comfortable with a nice amount of privacy with the curtain. The lockers and hooks in the room are also nice but beware that some of the beds have the outlet blocked due to a post. The downstairs bar area is nice and you get free welcome drinks to use at any time. As for the not so good stuff…all of the men that work there except Romeo are pretty much incompetent. The girls seem nice and knowledgeable as well but if you really need anything to get done talk with Romeo, he is the best. Everyone else pretty much really dropped the ball when it came to being of any help, especially the skater boy looking kid (you’ll know him when you see him). Also, there are tons of mosquitos in multiple rooms. They offer bug spray but it doesn’t really work and you will absolutely be guaranteed to leave the hostel with at least 6 bug bites

Unfortunately I can't recommend this place. The bed was so uncomfortable that I woke up each morning with a back pain. I also don’t know who thought that building those beds like that would be a good idea - my legs were under someone's bed so I constantly kept kicking the wall while moving my legs. Every move shook all four connected beds. Also, doors on the whole floor were so massive and loud that walls of the room literally shook with every closing/opening which made it very hard to fall asleep at night. The AC was very loud. The bathroom could use some improvements - my cosmetics kept falling off the shelf in the shower and the mirrors above the sinks are hung at wrong height (made it hard to access the sink while washing my face etc.). On the bright sides - I was able to keep my bed for an additional third night, the breakfast was big enough and tasty (unfortunately paid additionaly), the location was good and the neighbourhood seemed safe. The lift was working, the AC was strong, the reception crew was friendly, helpful and skilled in English. I wish this quality was at least cheaper for a night but well, Paris.

I only stayed for one night and have nothing to complain about, the room was clean and set up very well, toilets and showers are easy to reach and right around every corner is something interesting to discover - would come again!

The room I was in had 3 others already there. It was a mess with their things everywhere when I arrived. The bathroom floor had water all over from the shower (only a curtain between the rest of the bathroom), so to even go to the toilet was impossible without getting feet wet. I had to go and ask staff for some spare towels to mop up the water.
I was placed on a top bunk which was right next to the A/C unit which made weird noises on and off the whole night long.
Okay - it's a hostel, it's not going to be perfect, and a large part of your experience depends on the other individuals in your room (i.e. up to chance). Sadly the people in my room were messy and incosiderate.
The guy in the bunk next to me came crashing in at 2am, and when he got up in the night and early morning he jumped off his bed with a huge thud. The two other girls in the room played music on their phones as they got ready at 8am.

Overall I've stayed in better hostels where I had a better experience, cleaner rooms and a better night's sleep.

I was so tired and jet-lagged when I checked in at The People that I felt like a drunk toddler. But the staff members were so kind and understanding - they went above and beyond during my stay. The shared bunk rooms and bathrooms were incredibly clean, and the location is conveniently located a block or two from the Belleville Metro stop. I would book another stay here in a heartbeat.

The People - Paris Belleville Hostel is a good one. The bed is very comfortable and bathrooms are so clean and good. The rooms are new and clean. The people from reception are amazing. I really recommend it.

me and my friend came to paris for three nights and decided to book a hostel. we were pleasantly surprised by democratic prices for such clean and well-maintained rooms (curtains for privacy, lots of sockets, storage space, lockers, AC) - same goes to shared bathrooms, they were pristine! drinks and food at the bar downstairs were not pricey at all. the staff members are absolutely lovely, and so are the people who were staying in! we even made some friends in our room and down at the bar.

one of the best parts of the hostel was probably the rooftop. with such stunning view, it’s a great spot to relax, have a beer and admire the sunset.

thanks to the personnel - laid-back and understanding,- you guys made our holiday experience even better :)

The hostel was great. The location was super convenient, especially for metro access. The bar downstairs was a great feature, and made getting coffee in the morning so easy. The staff was super nice and friendly as well.

The rooms were great. We stayed in the rooftop dorm. The bed was comfortable, and the view from the roof was amazing. The rooms were really clean, and there was plenty of locker space.

Its the cleanest hostel ive stayed in my lofe. People here are lovely and helpful. Without a doubt i ll be staying here again. The only thing is that its a bit far from downtown but you have a metro 5 min walking.
The bets value for money!
Thanks for helping me have a lovely stay in Paris!

We had such a great stay at The People! The staff were so kind and welcoming, and extremely helpful when it came to accommodations and recommendations. The living space and bathrooms were clean, and I felt safe as a young female. Belleville is a bit out of the way from city centre, but I loved the little neighborhood and being farther back from the craziness of the tourist areas. Its a super quick walk to the metro which is VERY easy to use in paris! Would recommend this place to anyone looking for convenient and cheap accommodations

I was staying in a room with six beds due to limited budget, so I can't really complain about the size, but the staff are all very nice and the facilities are clean and tidy, the rooftop and the location is wonderful!

The only regret is that I just kept two shopping bags in my room without locking them in the locker as it was too late to light up the room to do that and I don't want to wake all my flatmates, and in the following day the two shopping bags were simply gone. It remained in doubt whether this was stealing or not as I still had all my valuable.

As I reported to those staffs for a few times they all did express their sympathy for my loss, and they also tried to let me to check the room where their cleaners keep all the findings. As you can guess I could not find them.

I understand that each staff has tried their best effort, but I really hope that they can really check the cctv for me, unfortunately I didn't think they have the time or probably not having enough staff to do that. I would be better if they actually open a case for this issue, so that I didn't have to be like telling the long story once again every time I saw a new poor staff who do not even know what is going on.

The bed and showers were excellent! Super comfortable, and clean. The staff was so kind, helpful, and patient. We especially loved the detail of the tile superheroes on the floor of the bar. One employee in particular, the man with a moustache, tried his very best to help us identify the superheroes. Even though he was wrong about Optimus Prime, that doesn’t change our view of the hostel as a whole. :)
1000000/10 would definitely stay again.

- Alison Argyle

Great experience for us! My sister and I are traveling around and stopped in Paris for a couple of nights. We stayed in a four bed mixed dorm and everything looked great! We had a bedroom on the top floor, which was also the roof, and it was an amazing view! The metro was about a block away in either direction and very easy to use to get to anywhere needed including to the train station and the airport. The downstairs doubles as a bar which had comfy seats and activities going on every night. I had the second shortest bed (still a bottom bunk) and found it slightly difficult to get in, so if you have any physical impairment, I would definitely request the shortest bed (which from what I saw with one of our roommates, they were very happy to work with). Staff was helpful and friendly and spoke good English - which was good because neither of us have much French.

Stayed 2 nights solo in mixed dorm. Had the 2nd lowest bed. Rooms are ok sized, not the smallest nor biggest. The lockers in the room were big enough for my humongus sized luggage + packbag. Toilet has a small smell, could be fixed with a freshener. Showers were wonderful. There is a hairdryer free of charge. There is air conditioning yet if u want to manage it you need to contact reception. First night my room was full and the air little funky but i think it was a smelly roomate. Reception isnt superfriendly. Welcomedrink is like 1 dl. Compared to other hostels the matress was little better than your avarage one so that and a good price might be bringing me back.

I loved this place, it was just what I needed - I stayed in a 6 women dorm and it was clean, air conditioned and each bunk had a little curtain around it so frankly I felt like I had a bit of privacy! The shower was warm and pretty powerful. The lobby and bar area was friendly and always full of people. I came home about 4am and buzzed and someone opened the door. It also felt pretty safe as to enter the rooms area you needed a card to open the doors. Would definitely stay again.

Les Piaules was an incredible place to stay. We were a young group of friends and the environment was perfect for our weekend. The hostel is very chic and comfortable, and they have a rooftop from which you can see the entire city. I would repeat 100%.

Amazing hostel. Well located. Friendly and capable people. Open until late hours, arrived at 2am with no problems. Clean, hot shower. Didn't try the breakfast because I didn't want to, but lots of people were there. Nice atmosphere in the lobby

I really enjoyed my stay at The People-Belleville. The room was clean, the bed was comfortable and the privacy curtains are a nice touch. The rooftop terrace is lovely and a perfect place to meet other travelers. The bar and patio downstairs were perfect also, and they have weekly live jazz music on Thursdays. The metro is only a few minutes walk away and connects you to the rest of Paris. I liked that this hostel is in a quieter area so you can sleep restfully. I would definitely return.

We were in a room for 4 people, it was very clean and with lockers. I lost my key of my locker and it was no problem, they directly fixed it. I also forgot my pass for our room when I went out, ''no problem!'' and they gave us another one. I really liked the stuff. Also the hostel was very clean, the bathroom and bedroom. The rooftop was very good with a view of the Eiffeltower. I definitely want to visit it again!

Lovely courtyard, excellent food & drinks, very helpful staff, very clean. etc. Note: Paris is huge, it takes at least 30-45 minutes to go ANYWHERE, so plan accordingly. I relied on Ubers and all my drivers were amazing and friendly. Also beware of your belongs at all times. its Paris.

Great Hostel !
The rooftop is incredible , the bar is amazing , and the rooms are really great !
I would like to highlight the attention of all your staff, but especially Amanda... very kind and friendly!

Lovely place to stay, great staff, great facilities and reasonable prices! There's a rooftop where you can see the Sacre Coeur and Eiffel Tower and a bar downstairs too with breakfast! Also felt really safe travelling alone. Merci beaucoup Les piaules

Cozy atmosphere and practical to the city centre (2 metro less than 10 minutes). I had a private dormitory with 4 friends and everything was well cleaned and even the bathroom was okay. Cozy atmosphere in the hall and the breakfast at 3 euros is perfect: a croissant/viennoiseries and coffee/tea. A perfect deal!

Had an amazing time here! It’s clean, people are nice and there is always something to do. Check in and out was very easy and clear. Would recommand it to everyone :) I was alone and didn’t felt alone here haha

We stayed here for 3 nights and absolutely loved it. The staff were so friendly and helpful, the communal area had a nice buzz and the room was lovely. The hostel is very near metro stations so it is easy to get around. The only down side is that there is no kitchen to prep your own food or picnics.

Really enjoyed my stay at Les Piaules. The staff were friendly and helpful (and spoke english). The bunk was comfortable and the bathrooms were clean. There’s a nice rooftop from which you can see the Eiffel Tower and the Sacré Coeur. There’s a nice bar on the bottom floor and they threw a karaoke night which was a lot of fun. They also have lockers for storing your stuff after check-out. The rooms were quite quiet at night so it was easy to sleep. They also give you the option to purchase a padlock for your locker so you know your stuff is secure. It’s a quick walk to 2 metro stations, a nice park, and lots of shops and restaurants. Overall, very lovely hostel!

Overall, this was a good Hostel. The people were friendly and the bar with food was a nice plus.

The showers in my floor were broken and seemed to only spew water at the hotest setting. My back was really dry from this when I returned home.

Otherwise though, everything from this hostel was great. Nice staff, quick check in, and comfortable bedding and lockers.

I think the hostel it's wonderful, the bed was veeery comfy, I had a lot of space for my luggage. Everything was nice from the beginning, from the moment Amanda warmly welcomed me and even after helped me with a lot of advices. All the people from the reception were very nice and kind and the atmosphere it's very lovely. They have a good breakfast, diverse drinks and all kind of special things during week evenings.

The location is really good. In the neighborhood you get to see the real Paris and it’s people. With the metro you get everywhere in no time.
The personal is really great. The facilities are awesome as well.

Helpfull employees, clean space, nice place to chill in the lobby.
Only the bedrooms are quite small. and there are only 2 showers and 3 sinks for a whole floor.
The hosel is abot 15 mins, by foot away fro ,,Republic'' here are some stores and good restaurants.
But don't take the breakfast deal. It contains only filter coffee and chocolate crossoints

Very clean rooms and bathrooms. I stayed in a mixed room over 4 nights and folks were respectful for the most part. Lockers fit carry on sized suitcase and then some. The bar on the first floor is a good place to meet other people, especially if traveling solo. Decent enough wifi to get some work done as well (took a zoom video call without issue). I walked almost everywhere, the location was perfect for me. Only suggestions would be to have a full length mirror in the rooms (behind the door maybe?) and a water station at the bar. Would definitely stay again.

Everything was great. The room was nice and the staff was wonderful! Everything was clean and the air-conditioning worked perfectly. The hostel is also located in a good neighborhood with good access to public transportation.

I really liked staying at this hostel. the staff was very kind and helpful. It was pretty close to the metro station Belleville, so it’s easy to travel around paris from here. The only things I’d change are the restrooms, on my floor there was only one shower and one toilet (there’s also urinals) and I’d prefer a little more space in the room, it gets crowded pretty easily. But overall had an amazing stay and well worth the price.

I had a nice experience staying in this hostel. The reception was friendly. The bed is spacious and comfortable. The location is also ideal since it is only around a 5-minute walk from the metro. There is a resto-bar in the reception area where you can have a nice beer and meet new international friends. One downside I found is that their lockers (where you can leave your things before and after check-out) are quite expensive. It is 4 euros/day.

Nice rooms, with a lot of storage space for your stuff. The beds have curtains that guarantee some privacy. Everything, including the bathrooms, was clean. Friendly staff, good atmosphere and tasty food. I would definitely recommend.

M from morocco 🇲🇦 It really was an amazing experience i met a lot of amazing people there from different nationalities also the staff was very friendly and the rooms are very clean and comfortable thanks for making my trip very special once ill be in Paris again I’ll go there without any doubt ❤️

I really enjoyed my stay there. I can definitely recommend ist. The terrace on top of the roof has a breathtaking view.
It is a little far away from the city center tho.
The breakfast is really good, and the staff is kind as well :)

Nice rooms, clean bathroom, good atmosphere, friendly staff! We even got a free upgrade from a room from 8 to a room of 4! Very close to the metro and situated in a cool neighbourhood with a lot of cafes and restaurants!

My stay at Les Piaules was great. People were friendly and willing to help. It was my first stay in a hostel room and I really liked it (except the snoring person in my room 😄). I highly recommend Les Piaules if you’re a solo traveller and willing to discover Paris!

It was my first trip to Paris, and I liked staying there, the staff members were very helpful and kind, They even offered me a welcome drink, which made my night and it was also one of my very deep sleeping after a very tiring day. Thanks guys!

I love this place. The bar has a great set up, the drinks are very affordable, they have a rooftop, the people there are really kind and the housing is good. It's my go-to place to organise my birthday every year

It was my first time in Paris and I am so glad I close Les Piaules to stay in. The prices are very fair. The staff was extremely kind and helpful with everything I needed. The rooms were clean and comfortable and I was very glad to use the hair dryer in the bathroom. The food and coffee were also very nice. The community inside was warm and fun and I enjoyed karaoke night. The view from the rooftop was unexpected and beautiful - there's a view of the Eiffel Tower and Sacré-Coeur. Thank you very much for being all that you are.

The staff is very nice, and the atmosphere too in general.

1.Sadly, as soon as I opened the bathroom, a table fall from the wall leaving open a very nasty hole in the wall.
2. The phone was disgusting, very very dirty. I didn't even put it close to my ear as it was SO dirty. That made me felt very unconfortable.
3. The curtains were not set right, looked like if they didn't clean the room before our arrive.
4. The glasses were dirty too. :/ and the bathroom had hairs in the wall and floor.
5. We asked for a couples room, but they were 2 single beds joined together with blankets (horrible for sleeping)

The staff told me to call them after I finishing eating so they can go check the issues (when I told them first I only noticed the hole in the wall), but they didn't showed up (tried reaching out by phone 5 times in the night but nothing).

As I only stayed one night, decided not to make a big deal and just mentioned these problems to the staff in the morning, and leave a review so the management can pay better atention to room maintenance.

Still, the staff is gentle, and the rest of the hotel is nice.

Had a really fun time. It was my first time going solo and I made some fun new friends. The bar is a nice place to spend your evening and the jazz night made it even better. Only negative point is that the first morning the shower was really cold but that was fixed.

Hostel was really great, would recommend to anyone. However, we weren’t allowed to open the windows in our room. This was not so nice in these COVID times because we shared the room with 6 other people.

At first night I was robbed in this hostel. My stuff was inside the locker locked with my own padlock and even that had been broked down?!?! My laptop and other electronic stuff were stolen. The guy in my room looked like junkie and the hostel didn't catch anyone else than me or him coming or leaving the room at that time it has happend by watching the security camera footage. The doors didn't close properly either so it could've been outsider too but the footage prooved it must have been him but the hostel didn't do anything about it. Even the police officer said this isn't the first time something like this happens in this hostel. Online they had good reviews so that's why I booked them. I appreciate tho how the staff were truly sorry about it and offered private room, free meal and drink and obviously refund but I still can not recommend this hostel to anyone and I would never go again myself. It was also emotionally draining experience.

I had a very nice time in this hostel and met very nice people. However I heard stories about a guy stealing in bedrooms and in common areas but its a big city and its Paris so dont forget to lock your stuffs when you stay there. I was staying in a girls dorm and felt pretty safe, everything was clean, in the bedroom I felt quiet warm in the in the morning. The neighborhood isnt the safiest but I didnt have any problem (as a woman alone). This hostel would be perfect if it had a kitchen but breakfast is pretty cheap and tasty. Nice place to stay if you plan to visit Paris. You get what you pay for.
Special mention for the staff of Les Piaules Nation who organised a karaoke night that I really enjoyed.
Thanks to the welcoming receptionnists who gave me good advices for my trip.

Staff were only friendly to locals. Rooms were too crowded. Expensive. other hostels are better. i booked a room with 4 bunk beds and was surprised that my room mates were men and i was the only female. so i requested to be transferred. They downgraded my toom to a 6 person room and it was too small.it was such a hassle to go out everytime i needed to go to the toilet.St. Christopher’s inn was better.

The hostel is very nice and has a good bar downstairs for coffee/ drinks/ socializing. My 6 bed dorm room was clean and I liked the bunk bed design that allowed for ample privacy/ light blocking. The bed was also quite comfortable. I particularly appreciated the large locker which actually fit all of my stuff nicely (unlike some hostels). I liked the location- further away from a lot of the typical touristy attractions in Paris, but a great area to walk around and very easily accessible to other areas of the city via public transport. I enjoyed my stay at Les Piaules and would consider it again when I come back to Paris!

Defenetly a place I want to return every time I am in Paris, I have stayed in other hostels but the atmosphere here is unique, the staff is so friendly (each and everyone), location is great with a truly parisian vibe not a fake turistic packed area, great and not expensive bar, easy connection to city center (20 mins by metro) Also have meet so many interesting people here.
Don't think and book it now!

I thought the hostel was really good and clean, the bar downstairs cool and cheap, and the personnel overall nice. BUT while staying there I got some stuff stolen from another person staying in the room, and they didn't do anything, they didn't call the police, they didn't offer me any sort of refund, or discount. I thought that is not the proper way to treat your clients.

The hostel was nice, it had a good bar downstairs to meet other solo travellers. It also has a nice rooftop, and the staff was really helpful. As a bonus, you get extra privacy in your shared room, with a small curtain to block the light which is great!

Great stay here! Staff was super friendly, the lobby was a social hub with karaoke the night I arrived and other events throughout the week, and they give you a free drink with your stay! The day lockers for rent, towels for rent, and personal lights and charging stations in your bedroom were great features. And the whole place was very clean, especially the bathrooms!

Staff were super friendly! Loved the cosy and inviting atmosphere of the reception / bar. You also get a free mini drink at the bar as a welcome.
Bathrooms were clean and bunk beds were clean and had own lighting and charging sockets.

Brilliant stay! Thanks

Fantastic place to stay! Visited a few night with some friends. The staff were so helpful, friendly and gave great recommendations. Absolutely visit the Cantine restaurant across the road, super cheap and yummy food! Breakfast at the hostel was a great deal. Rooms were lovely and clean as were the bathrooms. 100% recommend! Don’t forget to check out the balcony! Also the bar is cheap and the events are good!

I had a great time at Les Piaules! The installations were perfect for the price and the people were really friendly, guests and staff, especially Isabel in the cashier. Will definitely be coming back!

It is pretty quiet except for the bar. How the hotel was designed helped me as an introvert. Will be back again once I return to Paris. If you want to mingle with other travelers, you can do so by staying in the bar.

I had a nice stay at Les Piaules! Unfortunally, the first bed i got was allready used, and the second had dust on the small shelves by the bed. The bathroom was not so clean at all times eather. My personal locker was ruined ass well, so i felt like my stuff was somewhat unsafe in the dorm. But the atmosphere and facilities where great, and i would definitly consider going back there, if I go back to Paris. And the staff helped me because my phone got stolen, so that was really nice too.

Great staff, friendly, talkative. They make you feel at home from the beginning. The room was clean and comfortable. Conveniently located. Great parties and cool people everywhere. I will come back for sure.

Les Piaules is the best hostel I’ve stayed at yet. Everything was very clean and the staff was all wonderful. It was easy to meet people and is in a very convenient location. The rooftop terrace is also quite nice. I would have extended my stay if I could have, and definitely recommend it to anyone considering Les Piaules as an option!

I just loved my stay there , the stuff was super friendly and I met many cool people there. The rooftop was really nice as well. The bar and the entrance area was really cozy. The beds were comfortable as well

I was in La Piaules for four days, i had just came from another Hostel in London and after my last experience I wasn’t expecting much. So when i walked in to this facility i was beyond impressed. The front desk guy was really nice and he even took the time to recommend a good restaurant down the street for me, that was within my budget. He was also so easy to speak and joined in the conversation after I had run into another traveler who stayed in the last room i was in at the previous Hostel. The bathrooms are beyond clean, and immaculate. The rooms were just enough. A sturdy bed with a warm blanket and plenty of storage space ( i stayed in a 8 mixed dorm). I met this really sweet girl who had a thirst for travel and the other two were a daughter and father from Germany. We all got along and had some good conversations. I was beyond impressed with the facility and experience. They even have lockers to rent in the basement incase you want to lock your things up after check out if you have a late flight. This place will be hard to beat and surpassed my expectations on multiple levels.

Thank you guys!

The hostel is in a very nice neighborhood, next to the metro. Their bar at the ground floor offers a cheap and good breakfast till 11a.m. There is a nice rooftop next to the rooms of the 6floor in which you can go till 10p.m to not disturb.
The bathroom has a small hairdryer that stops every 5-10 seconds, so not really usefull. During the afternoon we wanted to take a shower but there wasn’t hot water, but it came back for the night and morning. You have to bring your own soap and towel or you can buy them at the front desk. Room was small but well organized and warm, with a small balcony.
It was a nice stay for two days, for longer stay you have to be a bit equipped :)

I loved my stay there. The staff is really nice and everything is so easy and positive, always something going on. The beds are comfortable and offer a lot of privacy. Bathrooms could‘ve been a little cleaner but nothing major. Would definitely come back! Thanks!

Stayed for a week in the 8 room dorm. Nice room set up with the curtains and large locker storage for bags. Large hostel with nice downstairs common area and even a rooftop spot with a decent view. Bathrooms bit lacking, but most of the time alright. Staff good, not exactly friendly like most hostels.. has more of a hotel feel, but still some are great.
Location is OK, if walking it will be quite far to most areas. If using the metro it is OK, will often need a transfer for most spots of interest though.

I stayed there for 4 nights, the staff is super friendly and the rooms are nice. It's near the subway, which is really convenient to visit Paris and, the rooftop is amazing too. I would definitely recommend staying there.

Beds are well separated and quite sturdy. Staff is helpful. There is people of all age, but averaging around the 30 y. o. Very nice place to make connections. Minuses are for the bar that closes after 1 AM and the most underwhelming breakfast I have ever had for 7 euros.

I stayed at Les Piaules Bellevile for 5 days. I had a great stay! Rooms and amenities were good, staff was friendly and helpful and multilingual, and its in a great neighborhood with easy access to public transit.

I had a great experience visiting this hostel. The beds are very comfortable, rooms are clean as well as the bathrooms. The staff were friendly and very helpful with any questions or requests! Loved my stay here!

It was really wonderful experience to stay here. People are very amazing. It's a good place to stay when you want mingle with other amazing travellers from other countries. Happy to recommend others. It's near to the old part of Paris which have beautiful neighborhood.

I need to preface that this is a fantastic hostel with lovely staff and upbeat/hip vibes. My room was clean, as was the hostel itself. It was decorated very cool, nice lounging areas and the rooftop is a huge bonus.

Here are the negatives:
- no towels (they come rented, at a cost)
- no soap in any bathrooms (esp. during COVID!)
- no communal kitchen
- no microwave/fridge
- no cutlery (or like things you may need for dinner, utensils)
- it gets VERY loud in the evenings with the music
- Idk about all the rooms but my room had a mosquito every single night and it made sleeping impossible
- I was also on the top bunk and you cannot control the heat/cooling in the room, you have to go down, so I was constantly hot.

The last 3 points are nitpicking, but expecting soap, towels and a kitchen is the BARE minimum out of a hostel experience (And I’ve been to many).

I’d say this: If you score a really cheap deal here and can live without the above, absolutely do it. It was a fantastic stay, even with some of the inconveniences. But, if those inconveniences may irritate you, as much as they did me (and you can splurge elsewhere), I would say explore that option. Cause for me cooking dinner at home was essential for budgeting reasons and that was a huge impediment (but I guess it’s also on me for not pre-checking, but I never would have thought a hostel doesn’t have a kitchen - that’s like hostelling 101!)

I was incredibly impressed by Les Piaules. Friendly staff, rooms that are clean and practical and the buzzing atmosphere were highlights of my trip. Combine that with the perfect location and a stunning rooftop view and you have the best hostel in Paris. I would advise reading the hostel's FAQ to ensure a comfortable stay.

Awesome helpful stuff a rooftop where you can do Yoga with beautiful view over Paris live Music in the evenings clean rooms easy to get to know travellors from all over the world Kicker place and a small garden to have dinner all in all I can just recommend this place!!! Thanks a lot au revoir merci a toi :)

I stay two nights. It is very good that you can check-in at any time after 3pm but during the second night that i paid for a shared bedroom only for girls (and it costed more than the 1st night for a shared 8bedrooms), we shared the room with a guy; so the hostel did not respect the policy or what they sell...
Wifi, food (adequate prices), bathrooms were ok and only one block from the station

The hostel was excellent
the bathrooms are super clean
As a person who often go to hostels, I can see the differences and Les piaules is very good
The rooftop is amazing with the beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower, Sacré ♡ et Paris la Défense
People are so nice
The bedrooms are very clean, and super chill, you can have your intimate area with a curtain
Lot of storage in the bedrooms
And the restaurant is not expensive and so good

I recommend this hostel
Every time I will come In Paris I will stay here :)

(photo of the view on the rooftop)

Overall, my stay at Les Piaules Belleville was fine but I wouldn't stay there again.

When I arrived my room/sheets were clean BUT the bed frame had footprints all over the roof of the bunk, and at the foot of the bunk as well where someone had clearly been resting their bare feet - which means it hadn't been wiped down. Normal times- not ok. During covid? Definitely not ok. I got bites all over my arm on night 1, changed to a new room on a new floor and got bitten *again* on night 2. I'm certain they were bed bug bites as they were in a line and red (unlike mosquito bites). Take note there's also no kitchen/fridge, which is pretty unusual for a hostel but that's on me for assuming there would be one.

For the positives - rooftop is beautiful! Great views. The staff are very friendly and sociable. The rooms themselves felt clean (also bonus points for the blackout curtains), and the shared washroom/shower was decent as well. There's also an elevator, which is handy. A key card is needed to enter the room section of the hostel which is nice for security, though the main floor of the hostel seems to be open to the general public.

Overall, nothing wowed me and with the bug bites and dirty bed I won't be going back unfortunately but there's room for improvement!

The rooms are very nice and always clean. The atmosphere was great, very easy to meet people. And they are taking COVID safe precautions. But the best was the staff; I ended up being extremely sick and the staff made sure to check in on me and that made the stay so much more personable. Thank you Les Piaules staff for taking care of me!! :)

Very nice hostel with nice environment and good vibe. It is clean and well located in the city. I really enjoyed my stay. The room are comfortable and nice, there is enough space to store your stuff.!

Overall the hostel was ok but the staff made it exceptional. It’s a good place for young people wanting to meet others and party. I was annoyed at how the a/c was controlled down in the lobby! I had to wake up in the middle of the night to ask the receptionist to turn off the a/c. It was set at 20 Celsius! Some more awareness of the room temperature would’ve been nice.

The hostel rooms/beds are decent with privacy curtains. However, the lockers are a bit narrow so you can't keep your carry-on luggage open inside. There aren't many good common areas to socialize like other hostels I've stayed at. It seems like many visitors here are just working remotely and/or doing their own thing and keeping to themselves, so not the best hostel to stay at if you're looking for new friends to explore with. It's a hit or miss in terms of atmosphere. There weren't any organized activities (at least the staff never mentioned any) and the staff weren't that friendly and trying to bring guests together. There were some nights in the hostel that were dead, others that were a bit better. It's a bit stingy that there isn't a storage room to keep your luggage in if you check in earlier/leave later for free. They charge per hour to keep your luggage somewhere.. I've never had a hostel charge to store your luggage. There are shared bathrooms on each floor, and it was a bit frustrating because the light was censored so it'd keep turning off during my shower. I was showering in the dark.

The staff was very nice and helpful. I also got a refound on 1/3 nights when I checked out after one night. I could not sleep for more than 30 min before waking upp because of nois and mosquitos. The bathroom and shower was disgusting and I rate the breakfast 1/10.

I give it 1/5 because of the nice and helpful staff, if it had not been for staff, I would have given it 0/5
Photo: One of many bug bites.

I was on a travel just for one day(and a half), but at Les Piaules I found everything I needed. The mood, the music, the view, the cleanness. The most important thing is kindness of all the staff that is so spontaneus.
By the way, if you plan to stay there even for one day, don't forget to order a red beer and a croque classic made by the blonde jolie with smiley eyes.

Enjoy Paris!

We stayed in Les Piaules in the private room with an ensuite. The room was on the rooftop so we had amazing views everytime we looked outside. Our room and bathroom were clean and comfortable. The only thing that bothered us a little was that one of the sheets had some dark stains on it and the space between the bunkbeds and the wall was not cleaned (we found a tortilla wrap in there). This is the only reason we didn’t give it 5 stars.
The breakfast was good and the other food as well. We liked the cheese plate especially!
The staff was also very friendly and helpful! One night we bought a bottle of wine and some cheese outside the hotel but we didn’t have cutlery, so they let us borrow knifes and wine glasses to eat at the rooftop terasse. They even opened our bottle for us because we didn’t have a cork screw!
The hostel is near two metro stations so you can be in the city center in 20 minutes, which is very good!
All in all we enjoyed our stay at Les Piaules thoroughly and would gladly stay there again!
Thank you for the hospitality!

Stayed for a night while visiting Paris for a weekend. It is next to 2 metro stations, very easily accessible and personally I love Belleville as an area. It is close to many beautiful places to visit in Paris without the overflow of tourists. Servixlce was kind and friendly. Room, bed and bathroom were very clean. Especially the bed was very comfortable with clean sheets, personal light and charging area, with cabinets for personal items. Downstairs area is also very lively with a nice bar and several events if you travel solo and want some socialising. Would definitely stay again

I just loved the hostel. Thank your for your very nice welcome, cosy beds, everything very clean, cool atmosphere and amazing rooftop view. Metro , shops and restaurant are very close. Waht a beautifull place.

The hostel is very well located in the Belleville borough in the center of Paris. The rooms are tidy and clean, as well as the bathrooms. The bar has a nice outside terrace and a friendly and easy going atmosphere. The view from the rooftop is just amazing.
